author: @bhaskartripathi
text: @Krish : I have an entirely different take on understanding statistics and the maths about Data. If one does not understands statistical properties of data such as multi-modality, multiscale behavior, entropy, non-linearity, heteroskedasticity, endogeneity and many other such concepts then one can only build thing layered superficial solutions which may or may not be helpful to your clients and fellow researchers. These are all core concepts which one must learn. One must agree and accept that the learning curve is not short. In Data Science, we must know as much about the Data as possible in addition to the traditional software engineering. Please do not teach shortcuts. We will be producing third grade, incompetent Data Scientists and ML engineers with this approach. AI is a gimmick. Only old school ML still solves the real problems.
